Nutanix GPT-in-a-Box

The Cisco Compute Hyperconverged with Nutanix GPT-in-a-Box solution takes the complexity out of adopting generative AI. It provides the steps for deploying the underlying infrastructure for this solution in a single box. This solution combines Cisco servers and SaaS operations with Nutanix software, using the most popular large language models (LLMs) to produce a fully validated AI-ready platform that can simplify and jumpstart your AI initiatives from the data center to the edge.

The solution offers three key benefits:

  • Simplicity: The solution offers both SaaS and on-premises management options and includes day-0 through day-N operations, including service profiles for compute, storage, and networking that is customized for Nutanix to help simplify and accelerate cluster deployment and deliver better performance and resiliency.

  • Flexibility: The Cisco Compute Hyperconverged with Nutanix solution addresses modern applications and use cases to offer multiple choices in Cisco UCS server deployment options, the latest accelerator and drive technologies, and SaaS innovations from two industry powerhouses, including integrations with the leading public cloud providers. Also, the solution incorporates Cisco best-in-class networking technology, including Cisco Application Centric Infrastructure (ACI) integrations, to enhance performance and resiliency for data-intensive workloads in hybrid cloud environments.

  • Resiliency: The joint solution uses only enterprise-grade components. Its augmented system protection includes a collaborative support model, proactive automated resilience and security capabilities, and support systems and case notes for faster triage. When log files are uploaded or case notes are generated, that information is shared, enabling enhanced collaboration among support teams to resolve issues faster and provide an improved customer experience. The policy-based approach minimizes human error and configuration drift, which results in consistent, reliable cluster deployments.

It also enforces an overall security posture through centralized authorizations to prevent tampering with configurations.

One of the most challenging and costly aspects of designing a traditional multi-tier solution is knowing how many resources will be needed over its lifecycle. This is where hyper-converged infrastructure solutions come into play. They offer a robust, scalable, and efficient IT infrastructure, simplifying data center management. In this presentation, we will walk you through an overview of hyper-converged infrastructure solutions and their components. Before we explore the hyper-converged infrastructure, let's first discuss the three different infrastructure types and their differences. First, there is the traditional multi-tiered infrastructure solution, also known as non-converged infrastructure. It requires that compute servers, storage, and networking components are individually configured and linked together. Next, converged infrastructure delivers all the separate components from the non-converged infrastructure into a single chassis ready to be used out of the box. This approach reduces costs associated with cabling, cooling, power, and infrastructure management and allows you to manage all components centrally. Finally, we have hyper-converged infrastructure, or HCI, a software-defined infrastructure solution that uses virtualization to combine compute, networking, and storage components into a single system managed by a hypervisor software layer. The hyper-converged infrastructure, or HCI, combines virtualization, computing, networking, and storage on a single platform. This approach lowers complexity and costs while enabling better scalability, flexibility, and agility in managing and deploying IT resources. It scales linearly and predictably due to its core architecture, which automatically redistributes data as you add new nodes using the built-in software -defined node expansion tool. Based on your future needs, you can add nodes that are storage-heavy, storage-only, or compute-only. You can add storage-heavy nodes if storage resources run out faster than compute. If more storage is needed, you simply add storage-only nodes. In this case, there is no need for an additional hypervisor license. If compute resources run out faster than storage, you can add compute-only nodes to support more VMs without adding storage to the cluster. The ability to purchase what you need in the short term and add more when required removes a lot of guesswork and friction when buying infrastructure. To deliver a hybrid multi-cloud solution, Cisco is partnering with Nutanix, which is built on combined leadership and application, data, and infrastructure management. The Nutanix Cloud Platform, based on its industry -leading HCI foundation, is now validated, certified, and integrated with Cisco Server Infrastructure to help enterprises accelerate their hybrid multi-cloud journey. Cisco Compute Hyper-Converged with Nutanix is a software platform built with simplified cloud operations in mind, both private and public. It allows expansion with flexibility and choice in Cisco servers. Finally, it allows you to keep systems running with augmented support, resiliency, and security capabilities. The solution contains the following components. First, the Nutanix Cloud Platform with Nutanix or VMware vSphere hypervisor support. Second, one or more supported Cisco UCS nodes for computing and storage with Cisco Intersight Infrastructure Service for system management. And finally, the Nutanix Cloud Platform combines the core elements of its HCI technology with additional cloud services. This enables automation and integrations, enabling you to build, manage, and optimize your infrastructure across on -premises, edge, and public cloud environments. Nutanix Cloud Manager is a software control plane for provisioning, operating, automating, and governing workloads across clouds. Nutanix Cloud Unified Storage is the distributed and software-defined storage solution that provides the scale organizations need to serve any workload anywhere. It enables the unified storage platform, which can provide block, file, and object storage services. Nutanix Cloud Infrastructure provides a complete software stack to unify your hybrid cloud infrastructure. It enables functionalities such as scale-out storage, Nutanix Acropolis hypervisor, virtual networking, disaster recovery, and container services. With all these components in mind, Nutanix simplifies your IT infrastructure with a cloud-like experience, delivering scalability, performance, and efficiency all in one platform. Using Cisco's hardware, Nutanix and Cisco provide a robust, scalable, and simplified hybrid cloud solution that transforms your infrastructure into an AI solution. In this presentation, you explore the basics of hyper-converged infrastructure solutions and the combination of Cisco and Nutanix solutions that can transform your IT infrastructure. Whether you're embarking on an AI journey by using hyper-converged infrastructure solutions, modernizing your data center, or simplifying IT management, Cisco HCI with Nutanix provides the flexibility, performance, and reliability you need to succeed. Thank you for watching this presentation on Cisco hyper-converged infrastructure solution and components. This reference architecture combines these elements:

  • Nutanix GPT-in-a-Box software-defined solution

  • Cisco Compute Hyperconverged C-Series servers

  • NVIDIA L40S GPU

  • Cisco Intersight standalone mode (no external fabric interconnect)

  • Systems management: Nutanix Prism

  • A range of the most popular LLMs
